args:
As a secret weapon to defeat Laxi, Eirene
controls Mascula's body and makes it attack.
When the prince and his allies end up in a
tight situation, the danger causes Mascula
to regain control and launch a counterattack.
Hell, they're back again—and they don't\nlook like they're in the mood to chat.
I recall reading an old tome once...
Ex Machina was evidently an organization\nof androids from a thousand years ago\nwho fought to protect all people.
They surface and go dormant every few\ndecades, fighting to put the land back in\nthe hands of those they serve.
Uh, wait. We're people, and so are the\nfolks in Grams, so why are they trying\nto kill all of us?
Ex Machina defines ＂people＂ only as those\nwho fled to a flying city a millennium ago.
So far as they are concerned, all of you\nfall into the category of ＂terrestrials,＂\nnot people.
I don't suppose there's any way for us to\nsimply reconcile with the people who live\nin that floating city?
Unfortunately, no one has ever seen them,\nwhich rules negotiation out as a tactic.
There is little to be said for a civilization\nwilling to watch from afar as they send\nweapons out to do their bidding.
Sounds like the androids are the ones\ngetting a raw deal here.
I agree, Luca, but we still can't turn away\nwhen they are indiscriminately attacking\nanyone who crosses their path.
Yeah, I know we can't afford sympathy for \nfolks who are tryin' to kill everybody.
Today, I will terminate their lead unit.\nOnce this happens, the bulk of their\nforces will be rendered powerless.
We'll be counting on you two,\nbut don't do anything rash.

*pant* *pant* Finally took 'em down.
Still, doesn't it seem like something's
different with them from before?
They're a lot more...gung-ho.
Yeah, this isn't the cautious approach they\ntook before.
Guess that means they're fighting for real.\nWe better come up with a new plan in that\ncase, 'cause we can't keep up with this.
We will do something about it.\n▷We've located their lead unit,\nand we're heading out to stop her!◁
I'm counting on you both.\nLuca, let's clear a path for Laxi!
Oh, I'm a path-clearing MACHINE!\n...Er, a figurative machine, I mean.
Switching to Eden mode.\nI'll finish this fast!
Mana density is dropping sharply;\nshe's clearly switched to Eden mode.\nAre you ready, Finni?
Why would you ask such a thing?!
You're dodging the question; you know I've\nbeen running out of control a lot recently\nand you've been forced to stop me.
But what happens if you CAN'T\nstop me at some point?
If my heart is broken, what happens?\nWill I run amok destroying everything?\nWill I destroy...you?
Just the thought of doing that\nmakes me want to scream.
Do you remember our promise, Finni?
We promised to always be together,\nuntil the day we both break down.\nRemember?
Of course I remember.\nI'd never erase that memory.
Then you know I will never abandon you.

I have visual confirmation of the lead unit.
Commencing attack.
▷Laxi, someone is approaching at VERY
high speed from our left!◁
Understood. I will intercept that one fir...\n*gasp*!
Laxi, are you okay?! Leave the small fry\nto us and just take care of the lea...\nOkay, what the HELL?!
▷Or more precisely, it's my body.\nThe one that was stored in the Halidom.◁
Dammit, what are we supposed to do?!
▷Oh, no. Because of my body, Luca was...\nI have to do something, but...◁
Mascula, get it together!\n▷I...I know. That body isn't me.\nAnd yet, I can't help...◁
▷Was it because I'm hesitating?! Damn!\nI KNOW that body isn't me, but I just can't\nstop thinking about it!◁
This is the moment I've been waiting for!
Using that body allowed us to disrupt\nthe synchronicity their hearts require\nto maintain Eden mode.
▷So this was your doing?\nYou went to the trouble of stealing my\nbody just to cause this?!◁
That's right. I'll do whatever it takes!
I will have your heart...\nI will have them BOTH!
Because even androids have things\nthat are important to them!
HoStILe TaRgEt InTeRFerInG WiTh\nOpeRaTiOn. InITiaTinG TerMiNAtioN.
Dammit! I don't want to harm\nMascula's body!
I won't let you interfere with Irene!
Ugh, dammit... I screwed up...\nI can barely move...
▷No! My body...\nI'm going to kill Luca...!◁
You don't have time for distractions.\nAlthough, if it means you're giving up,\nthat's good news for me.
TerMiNaTinG HoStiLe. I WiLL DeLiVeR\ntHE FiNiShInG bLoW.
▷(I'm going to...kill Luca...\nNo! I won't let that happen! I won't!)◁
Hey, quit with the stalling and take\nthat long-eared guy out already.
I WON'T LET YOU DO IT!
Why is that body out of my control,\nand how is it conscious?!
Mascula, are you manipulating\nyour body remotely?
▷Yes, I'm controlling myself—\nalthough I have no idea how.◁
Laxi, now! Hurry up...and...\nDeSTRoY ThIS BoDy!
▷I don't know know how I'm able to\ncontrol my body, Laxi.◁
AnD I AlSo don't know how long I'll be\nAbLe to Do tHiS. Destroying it is the OnLy\nWaY!
Are you sure? It might mean you'll never\nbe able to go back to the way you were...
That's fine. I mean, yes, it would be\nwonderful to go back to how things were\nand have my own body again...
But there are things in my life that are\nso much more important than that.
The body isn't me—what IS me is the\ndesire I hold to protect my friends!
And I'd rather lose my own body than\nlose what really matters to me!
Understood...but we do this together.\n▷Right! Let's go!◁
